This folder contains example that demonstrates periodic boundary condition for 
the free surface. Initial free surface topography perturbation is unsymmetric, 
which leads to unequal surface uplifts on both sides of the domain with free 
slip boundary condition. With periodic boundaries both ends rise with the same rate.

Running the example involves 2 steps:

    1. Create topography file with GeophysiclModelGenerator package
    
       julia periodic_create_topo.jl

    2. Run the LaMEM file in parallel
    
       mpiexec -np 16 ../../bin/opt/LaMEM -ParamFile periodic_surface_test.dat

And as always, you can use ParaView to visualize the results.
